cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.AR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless communication networks and their impact on smartphones. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the maximum receiving rate of smartphones in 5G networks, which involves information theory concepts. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the impact of computation overhead on multimedia applications in smartphones. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the impact of the maximum receiving rate of smartphones on the control systems of 5G networks. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the hardware architecture of smartphones and their impact on 5G networks.
